<emphasis box="[533,747,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Robinsonia drechseli</emphasis>
Laguerre
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[851,934,728,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[851,927,728,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[947,965,727,751]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">A</emphasis>
ventral view, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1109,1126,728,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">B</emphasis>
dorsal view, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1263,1281,727,751]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">C</emphasis>
lateral view, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1418,1436,728,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">D</emphasis>
valva view from inside, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[397,414,764,788]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">E</emphasis>
aedeagus with everted vesica
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,834,1004]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,834,860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[414,553,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1506,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1028,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-159@9.[151,1436,1028,1483]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 13. A–C: female genitalia of Robinsonia drechseli Laguerre sp. nov., A ventral view, B dorsal view, C detail of the antrum, ductus bursae and papillae anales." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982860" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982860/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Fig. 13A–C</figureCitation>
). Papilles anales convex in middle. Apophyses anteriores slightly shorter than the posteriores. Pheromone glands straight and tubular, prominent. Antrum very slightly sclerotized. Ductus bursae as a flat ribbon, short and strongly curved. Bursa copulatrix small and pyriform, with circular wrinkles and two signa shaped as a fold in the center of a circular spiculate area. An accessory hemispherical wrinkled bursa, slightly smaller than the main bursa. The two bursae joined by a slightly scobinated tubular connection.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982860" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4982860" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982860/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" startId="9.[151,250,1506,1530]" targetBox="[151,1436,1028,1483]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1506,1567]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,344,1506,1531]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">FIGURE 13. A–C</emphasis>
: female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laguerre" authorityName="Laguerrre" authorityYear="2021" box="[556,868,1507,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drechseli" status="sp. nov.">
