</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1613,1783]" box="[199,477,1613,1639]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1613,1639]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Early stages</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1613,1783]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1649,1675]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of its collector Ulf Drechsel for his large contribution to the 
<collectingCountry box="[1259,1363,1649,1675]" name="Paraguay" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
fauna knowledge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1613,1783]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1721,1747]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Distribution.</emphasis>
Presently only known from 
<collectingCountry box="[688,792,1721,1747]" name="Paraguay" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
essentially in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1006,1145,1721,1747]" country="Paraguay" name="Alto Parana" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Alto Parana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1160,1258,1721,1747]" country="Paraguay" name="Caazapa" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Caazapa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1272,1386,1721,1747]" country="Paraguay" name="Cordillera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Cordillera</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,268,1757,1783]" country="Paraguay" name="Amambay" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Amambay</collectingRegion>
departments, 
<emphasis box="[426,467,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">i.e.,</emphasis>
in the East of the country.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1829,1999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
During a visit to the MWM in München, we found a strange, large 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laguerre" authorityYear="2021" box="[903,1031,1829,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,1031,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Robinsonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen close to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schaus, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mera">
<emphasis box="[1244,1437,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Robinsonia mera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schaus, W." box="[159,310,1865,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="189 - 211" refId="ref8768" refString="Schaus, W. (1910) Descriptions of New Heterocera from Costa Rica. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 8, 6, 189 - 211. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931008692838" type="journal article" year="1910">Schaus, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[386,507,1865,1891]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
but collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[691,742,1865,1891]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Peru</collectingCountry>
near Pozuzo (
<collectingRegion box="[900,1078,1865,1892]" country="Peru" name="Pasco" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Pasco Province</collectingRegion>
). The sequence of this specimen confirmed the vicinity of the two species but the distance of 7.06 % implies that we had in hand a new species. After a close examination of the de Toulgoët’s Collection housed in MNHN we found five additional specimens, including the only known female and we describe this species below under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Laguerre" authorityName="Laguerrre" authorityYear="2021" box="[973,1336,1973,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inexpectata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[973,1231,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Robinsonia inexpectata</emphasis>
Laguerre
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1343,1430,1973,1999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1343,1430,1973,1999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
